A man was shot in the face in Queens Friday night, police said. A mystery gunman pulled the trigger on his 37-year-old male victim around 8 p.m. at 130 Street and 9th Avenue in College Point, an intersection that lies at the opening of Powell’s Cove Park. The man, suffering from a single gunshot wound, was rushed to Booth Memorial Hospital in stable condition. The shooter — who was only described as male — fled in an unknown direction, according to cops. The investigation is ongoing.